  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nanvil 0.1.0 (4604a42 2022-05-12T00:04:28.605557+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n`block.timestamp` is always `1` when interacting with contracts via an Anvil fork node (`anvil --fork-url https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/api_key_here`).\r\n\r\nAs an example, call `getCurrentBlockTimestamp` on the [multicall contract](https://etherscan.io/address/0xeefBa1e63905eF1D7ACbA5a8513c70307C1cE441) to reproduce this behavior.",
